The course presupposes the Council of Europe Level A2.
Vocabulary and grammar studied during the course are related to the following topics:
- sport and health;
- character and personality;
- stress and its reasons;
- new technologies;
- French social codes;
- comparison of different cultures;
- regional linguistic variety in Francophonie (Québec, Belgium, etc.);
- different language registers (formal vs informal);
- consumer culture vs ecological choices;
- sharing own experiences, expressing preferences, talking about habits and activities;
- the younger/older generation;
- working conditions, values and possible conflicts.
Grammar will focus on past tenses, relative pronouns, future and conditional.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This pre-intermediate course aims to develop the reading, conversational and listening skills of the students and their knowledge of grammar while focusing on the training of oral communication. The course may be carried out by a native speaker.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course the student will have developed his readiness to communicate in French, his oral and written expression and comprehension skills will have improved towards more clarity and fluency, due to his enriched vocabulary and better pronunciation.
